  "text": "Extraction of carotenoids from bacteria and plants followed previously described protocols [CITATION_1] . Saponification of flower pigments was done in ethanol:KOH (60% [w/v]) 9:1 overnight at 48C. The carotenoids were separated with di-ethyl-ether following addition of NaCl to a final concentration of 1.2%. Analysis by HPLC was previously described [CITATION_2] . Carotenoids were identified by their characteristic absorption spectra and typical retention time, which corresponded to standard compounds of lycopene, b-carotene, and zeaxanthin. Carotenoid quantification was performed by integrating the peak areas using Millennium chromatography software (Waters).",
